West 9th Street, south side, east from Henry Street, showing in the foreground the new structure of the Bushwick Can Company.

View 2 shows the houses seen beyond the Can Company's plant in view 1, extending to the corner of Clinton Street. All the buildings in views 1 (excepting the Bushwick Can Company's) and 2 were later razed to make way for the Red Hook low rent housing project, sponsored by the New York City Housing Authority.

June 9, 1938
